{"id":"counsellor","term":"Counsellor","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>An adviser (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 11:14\">Prov. 11:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 15:22\">15:22</a>), a king’s state counsellor (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 15:12\">2 Sam. 15:12</a>). Used once of the Messiah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 9:6\">Isa. 9:6</a>). In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Mark 15:43\">Mark 15:43</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 23:50\">Luke 23:50</a>, the word probably means a member of the Jewish Sanhedrim.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Proverbs 11:14","Proverbs 15:22","2 Samuel 15:12","Isaiah 9:6","Mark 15:43","Luke 23:50"]}